What you need to know:

In December 2014 German broadcaster ARD alleges systematic doping in Russian athletics.It provokes the resignation of Russian athletics chief and the treasurer of the International Association of Athletics Federations (IAAF), Valentin Balakhnichev and the IAAF's marketing consultant Papa Massata Diack, the son of then-IAAF president Lamine Diack.The World Anti-Doping Agency (WADA) sets up an independent commission headed by its former chief, Dick Pound, to investigate the claims.